Chen suffered the severe brain injury in a car accident when he was 17 and spent months in intensive care in hospital. 

While his body recovered, his memory loss is still so severe that he often forgets things that happened between five and 10 minutes ago.

The debilitating condition also means that Chen cannot remember how to write properly, so he makes notes in a phonetic 'scrawl' that mostly only he understands.

'This is my record, I write in it everyday, even if it is pouring down with rain or if I don't go out to do the weeding I still l must write, "Heavy rain",' he said. 

'Whenever I get home from any time away  I quickly grab my notebook and write down important things from the day - who I've met, what I've done, how much money I got from recycling bottles, all that sort of stuff.'

